               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-328-person2280">
                  GEORGE 
                  JOSEPH FORD
               <interp inst="t18310630-328-person2280" type="surname" value="JOSEPH FORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-328-person2280" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-328-person2280" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 12th of June, about eight o'clock in the evening, I was in <placeName id="t18310630-328-crimeloc1720">Mitre-passage, Hatton-garden</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-328-crimeloc1720" type="placeName" value="Mitre-passage, Hatton-garden"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310630-328-crimeloc1720" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-328-off1718 t18310630-328-crimeloc1720"></join>, with my wife on my arm, and felt a tug at my outside coat pocket - I felt a shoving against the wall, and in a moment Grant and another man passed; I recollect seeing him behind me in Hatton-garden - I missed my handkerchief; I went to Grant, and said, "Give me my handkerchief;" he said, "I have not got your handkerchief," and swore - I then saw Green run away; he almost knocked my wife down in running; I followed, calling Stop thief! a gentleman came up - I asked him to hold him while I went after the other, and at the bottom of the court two lads said a fellow had run up there with a handkerchief; I went up - it is no thoroughfare, and Green came out; I called him, and said, "Give me my handkerchief;" he said, "I have not got it" - his coat came open, and it fell out; I got a Policeman, who took him - there was a third man, who got away.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310630-328-person2281">
